    # [Scene: Municipal Green Atrium | Night — Emergency Hearing]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fast, driving strings; percussion like a heartbeat racing toward a peak]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A chorus of murmurs, camera shutters, and a distant storm hitting the city]
    "You stand beneath the atrium lights and feel like a lighthouse for a shoreline that has been asking for one. The cameras pick up the salt on your collar, the frayed edge of your field jacket."
    "You can taste metal at the back of your tongue — adrenaline and the tang of high tide. The leak is no longer just a file in your pocket; it has teeth. It has made the"
    "city look at itself."
    "Nora is beside you, breathing small, precise breaths. Samir stands with his hands folded, an island of slow motion in the electric room. Across the chamber, Ari’s posture is clean as a blueprint; he is surrounded"
    "by counsel with their suited armor. He meets your eyes once — and in that second there is a hundred lectures you both took, a thousand semesters in shared labs, and a gulf built from different"
    "certainties. His face is unreadable to everyone else and not to you. Unreadable can mean many things; now it means the question you have already answered and the consequence you must carry."
    "Councilwoman Elena rises to call the session. Her voice is official and thinly warm; microphones pick up the fine grain of her politeness."
    show councilwoman_elena_reyes at left:
        zoom 0.7

    councilwoman_elena_reyes "This emergency hearing will address allegations raised in the recent disclosure. We will hear testimony, receive evidence, and consider immediate protections."
    "A reporter lunges forward. A dozen phones point like compasses. Someone shouts for restraint; order tries to assemble itself but the room is a hitching stage of competing truths."
    "You feel every pair of eyes like tide marks. Your chest tightens into a small drum. The leak was meant to make the hidden visible — and now visibility is avalanching into action."
    hide councilwoman_elena_reyes

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The rain escalates outside to a thudding percussion that vibrates the glass]
    "You are called to speak early. You walk forward with the steadiness you have learned in late-night marsh surveys and community repairs — the steadiness of someone who has carried tools through drowned doorways. Your voice comes out steadier than you feel."
    show maya_ortega at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_ortega "The information we released is not theater. It is a map of choices already made for and against our neighborhood. People here have weathered loss and pieced together lives: boats, kitchens, birthdays. We are not abstractions on a spreadsheet."
    "Ari Nakamura rises to object. His voice is measured, practiced."
    show ari_nakamura at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_nakamura "Ms. Ortega, the firm acted within contracting scope. We prepared scalable defenses which would protect the largest number of people. Accusations do not replace context."
    "He gestures to a glowing model beside him — a sleek seawall, a digital canopy. It gleams like an offered absolution."
    show nora_daz at center:
        zoom 0.7

    nora_daz "He’s selling futures in a package. Make them feel the present."
    "You remember Samir’s words from the Hub — 'Truth can build a house. Truth without structure can blow a roof off.' You watch Ari’s advisors shift; one of them is suddenly sweaty at the temple. The room hums with the kind of pressure that bends petty things into policy."
    hide maya_ortega
    show councilwoman_elena_reyes at left:
        zoom 0.7

    councilwoman_elena_reyes "We will call for an immediate oversight review. Project approvals will be paused. There will be emergency protections for at-risk residents while an independent audit proceeds."
    "The words land like a buoy thrown into stormwater. Heads tilt. Phones start shouting headlines into the world."
    "Ari inclines his head; it is the only concession he makes before the lawyer at his side launches into a defense about process, procurement, and precedent. The sound of lawyers is a practical ocean — necessary but impersonal."

    menu:
        "Lock eyes with Ari and point out the human cost":
            "You meet Ari's gaze and speak his name. The chamber listens when you make his project talk about the porches and not the profit. Ari’s face flickers—annoyance, then something like recognition."
        "Turn and address the community on the screens":
            "You turn to the live feed and speak into thousands of living rooms. The chat fills up with messages of support and people tagging their homes' coordinates. You feel the room tilt toward the public when the faces of neighbors appear on screen."

    # --- merge ---
    "The moment you choose, the atrium swells around it; whichever way you direct the energy, it multiplies. The oversight vote is set. Journalists file details that will unsettle investors and activate watchdogs. Ari's firm braces for audits and legal headaches; the door to the top-down solution narrows."
    "After hours of testimony — people speaking with river-slow cadence and scientists in clipped pulses — the vote passes: an emergency moratorium on project approvals that could displace residents; an independent audit; a temporary fund allocated"
    "to immediate repairs and relocation only where absolutely necessary. It is not everything you wanted. It is everything that can be bought with the pressure you and your people applied."

    "Outside the Atrium, during a break, someone hands you a grim-smiling sandwich and a stack of messages. One is from an old municipal contact" "We'll need you to testify at a wider hearing next week; there's also interest from a foundation for a scaled program — but they want you to be named lead consultant and sign non-disclosure."
    "Ari catches you in a hallway lined with glass planters. The air smells faintly of damp soil and machine polish. He speaks quietly, away from microphones but not away from consequence."

    ari_nakamura "Maya—this could have been handled without a public pitchfork. We could have negotiated protections into the work."
    "You can hear the things he doesn't say: that his career will now be audited; that his expensive visions might be stalled; that he suspects you made a moral calculus that cost him as well. There"
    "is fatigue in his eyes — not like yours, which is threaded with salt freckles, but a professional weariness."
    hide ari_nakamura
    show maya_ortega at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_ortega "Negotiation is a privilege when your neighbors aren't on the move list. I have seen what non-disclosure looks like from this side. I can't— I won't make that calculus with someone else's home as the variable."
    hide nora_daz
    show ari_nakamura at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_nakamura "You always were more stubborn than I expected. And more stubborn than I deserved."
    "The exchange piles into the chamber's chorus: cameras, footsteps, a city recalibrating. You don't ask for forgiveness and he doesn't offer it. There is a chance — a small, honest one — for mutual respect. It is not romance. It is not agreement. It is an honest bookend."
    # [Scene: Old Docks Community Hub | Night — Aftermath]
    hide councilwoman_elena_reyes
    hide maya_ortega
    hide ari_nakamura

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A layered rhythm that mixes relieved laughter with lingering adrenal bass]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The smell of frying oil, wet canvas, and the neighbor’s radio playing a low brass tune]
    "The Hub becomes the eye of another storm — this time a swarm of neighbors returning from the atrium, from television studios, from the river of social media. Your inbox is full of offers and threats."
    "Some funders reach out with compromises; developers whisper about lawsuits. But the strongest sounds are older: Samir telling a story about a tide that turned when the community worked a night shift to repair a seawall,"
    "Nora mapping a patch schedule for the coming weeks, Luca — who appears after the vote — slapping a hand into yours as if the act could transfer solid ground."
    show luca_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    luca_chen "We did the thing that makes people get up on porches and help. We'll be messy and slow, but it's ours."
    "You feel the word 'ours' like a settling; it anchors you in a way public accolades never could."
    show nora_daz at right:
        zoom 0.7

    nora_daz "We have at least three more hacks to keep water out of Susana’s bakery this week. Samir says if the council's fund holds, we can finally raise the new marsh garden bed off the path."
    show samir_qureshi at center:
        zoom 0.7

    samir_qureshi "The law has given us a span. The work now is to make that span into a place where memory grows. That is labor not measured by grants."
    "Conversation here is long and full of small turns: complaints about logistics, sudden plans, and laughter that comes from relief rather than triumph. You realize, in one warm breath of the Hub, that this is the"
    "victory you wanted. It is not a single wall but a thousand hands making a thousand small defenses."

    menu:
        "Take the mic and call for a volunteer brigade for repairs":
            "You stand, your voice threading through strings of conversation. People nod and write names. There is a fierce, practical joy as schedules are crossed off and tools assigned."
        "Sit back and let Nora organize the brigade":
            "You sit with your cup, thankful for the warm weight of it. Nora runs the room with efficient humor; you listen and a certain calm returns to your shoulders."

    # --- merge ---
    "Even as the community asserts agency, consequences settle on you. The municipal foundation that once courted your name pauses its offer when legal counsel tightens — you are now entangled in a public dossier that makes"
    "big, risk-averse organizations cautious. A coveted research fellowship withdraws its offer. You lose the chance at a platform that could have scaled your living shoreline model quickly. Money that would have amplified your experiments flows elsewhere."
    "The professional diminishment arrives like a ledger balancing: the city protects the people and closes doors on you."
    "It stings less than you expect and more than you fear. Your identity — the engineer who wanted to build for many — feels narrower now, but also more honest. You have traded broad reach for rightness on the ground."
    # [Scene: Salt Marsh Reserve | Dawn — Weeks Later]
    hide luca_chen
    hide nora_daz
    hide samir_qureshi

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Quiet, swelling strings that move toward a gentle, resolute climax]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Ocean breath, gulls, the wet slap of boots in mud]
    "The final movement begins not in a chamber of glass but in the mud. Months have passed and the audit has produced uncomfortable headlines. Ari's firm pays fines and is required to rework procurement rules. Oversight"
    "boards are installed. Municipal policy adds rights for community voices in major projects. The city will not immediately become a paradise of equity, but structures that once smoothed over displacement are now held to light."
    "You kneel across from Samir and press a reed into wet earth. Fingers cold, you feel the small friction of root and soil. Around you, faces—old and young—work with an energy that is neither frantic nor fearful but fierce in its steadiness."
    show samir_qureshi at left:
        zoom 0.7

    samir_qureshi "We plant like we vote. One small stake today holds a line tomorrow."
    "Nora wipes mud on her palms and grins; Luca Chen hums a repair song as he threads rope around a bundle of seedlings. The ritual is ordinary in its holiness: songs, stories, coffee, a shared set"
    "of tools. The community ritual continues — unbroken. You breathe it in and let it settle into your bones."

    "There are losses. The scope of your projects is smaller, the accounts thinner, and your name is less attractive to financiers who demand glossy deliverables. But the marsh belongs to people who will keep tending it; the bakery on the corner stays. Susana hangs a new sign" "Repaired by the Neighborhood."
    "Ari visits the marsh once, not to argue but to see. He stands at the edge of the reeds and watches as volunteers braid willow stakes. He approaches you at the end of the day, his"
    "sleeves already speckled with mud — an offering, perhaps, to the authenticity he once undervalued."
    show ari_nakamura at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_nakamura "You made us accountable. I thought we could pare risk with metrics and design, but metrics don't hold a hand while a roof goes up."
    show maya_ortega at center:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_ortega "You helped build things people could use. But you forgot that people are not variables. They are reasons."
    "Ari studies your face as the last light slips. There is admiration threaded with regret. He bows his head, not as defeat but as recognition."

    ari_nakamura "I will see the audit through. I will try, in the ways you taught me, to listen elsewhere."
    "He does not ask for you to lead his projects. He does not try to romanticize the moment. This is not a reconciliation of hearts; it is the slower, steadier recompense of one professional recognizing the cost he helped create."
    "You watch him go back toward the skyline. The tension between duty and intimacy finds a quiet compromise: not a union, but a mutual reconstituting of priorities."
    hide samir_qureshi
    hide ari_nakamura
    hide maya_ortega

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Builds to warmth; brass and strings swell into a hopeful chord]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Hammering, laughter, the soft roar of the repaired tide]
    "- Volunteers shore up small stretches of shoreline with living barriers while city funds pay for emergency bulkheads only where people must be moved."
    "- You teach workshops on marsh restoration to eager teenagers who measure tides with your battered wristband."
    "- Ari’s firm retools procurement guidelines and loses some clients; they become smaller and more cautious."
    "- Funding is spotty. Nights are long. But the rhythm belongs to you: community meetings, hands dirty, immediate repairs saved from displacement."
    "Samir hands you a small, rough charm — a length of braided reed tied into a ring."
    show samir_qureshi at left:
        zoom 0.7

    samir_qureshi "For remembering. For when you doubt what you gave up."
    "You slip it into your notebook. It sits beside a list of sites to plant next week. It is less glamorous than a grant letter, but it presses like a compass against your palm."
    hide samir_qureshi

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Gentle, conclusive; a single sustained chord that feels like both rest and readiness]
    "You have fewer invitations to lecture halls with polished panels, fewer offers that carry the word 'scale' with promises of renown. You have, instead, late-night planning sessions with neighbors, breakfasts of leftover repair biscuits, and the"
    "knowledge that when the tide comes heavy, the people you love will not be an afterthought."
    "There is grief for what could have been — a larger program, wider recognition — and there is a fiercer joy. You chose to make your work tethered to the people and not to the podium."
    "That choice has a cost and a clarity. That clarity becomes its own kind of triumph."
    # [Scene: Salt Marsh Reserve | Sunset — The New Ritual]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_7 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Warm harmonies; a single cello sings under the voices]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Lanterns clinking, quiet singing, the tide whispering against the new fiber]
    "Samir stands and speaks — not as an elected official but as a keeper of story."
    show samir_qureshi at left:
        zoom 0.7

    samir_qureshi "We may not have every bank or every bureau on our side, but we have each other, and that is not small."
    "You feel the whole thing fold into you: the hearing’s thunder, the atrium’s glare, the long slow months. A very loud, very bright sequence of storms led you here. And standing at the water's edge, watching"
    "neighbors secure lanterns so they do not drift away, you understand the shape of your victory."
    "It is messy. It is slower. It is wholly yours."
    "You have less fame and more trust. You will no longer be courted by projects that demand silence; you will be called upon to teach, to patch, to listen. Sometimes the work is repair. Sometimes it is translation between angry stakeholders. Mostly, it is presence."
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Swells into a final, warm chord]
    hide samir_qureshi

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_8 at full_bg
    "You close your eyes for a moment and let the sound of the marsh — gulls, breath, the soft slap of the tide — fill you. You have traded broad acclaim for deep belonging. You have"
    "traded promotion for a porch-light whose beam moves when the city turns. Your name may be less on plaques, but it is embodied in the hands that pass ropes, in the pastry that stays warm in"
    "Susana’s oven, in the seedlings that will one day be a small, impenetrable reed wall."
    show nora_daz at left:
        zoom 0.7

    nora_daz "Not bad for a night's work."
    "You let yourself laugh — full and relieved. The laughter is a tide that proves something important: that joy can be urgent and loud, that triumph can sound like a drill and a song at once."
    "You feel, finally, the weight of the choice settle into something like rightness. The leak was not an erasure; it was a relay. You passed the truth to the public and let the public decide, and the public chose to protect the people you love."
    hide nora_daz

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_9 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: One long, sustaining note that turns to silence]

    scene bg ch12_f99e88_10 at full_bg
    "THE END"
